apiBySlugifiedNameAndOwnerName.name: Fresh LinkedIn Profile Data
apiBySlugifiedNameAndOwnerName.title: Fresh LinkedIn Profile Data
apiBySlugifiedNameAndOwnerName.description: Real-time LinkedIn Data. Search Employees at Scale. Get Access to Sales Navigator without cookies. Trusted by numerous AI startups around the world.
apiBySlugifiedNameAndOwnerName.longDescription:
✅ Unofficial LinkedIn API for retrieving any type of LinkedIn data..

✅ Launched in 2022, and become the most **reliable & scalable** API for LinkedIn scraping.

️✅️️️ Search employees or companies in real-time, at scale, **without using any cookies**.

️✅️ **Unique Feature**: Be able to [fully automate LinkedIn Sales Navigator scraping](https://fdocs.info/tutorial/howto-search-leads) without the need for **cookies or accounts**. Capable of scraping hundreds of thousands of leads daily.

✅ **100% Refund Guarantee:** If you use up to **10% of your credits** and aren’t satisfied, we’ll give you a **full refund**—no questions asked.

✅ **Trusted worldwide** by numerous AI-related startups.

✅  **[External API Documentation](https://fdocs.info/)** for detailed instructions and reference.

✅ **Fast & Professional Support:** Contact us at [support@fdocs.info](mailto:support@fdocs.info).

readme.text:
### FAQs

#### How fresh is your data?
We scrape data directly from LinkedIn at the time you make a request, ensuring real-time, up-to-date information.

#### What is the difference between a credit and a request?
Our API uses a credit-based system. While every API call (request) counts as one call, each call may consume a different number of credits depending on the complexity of the task or the specific endpoint used.

#### Do unused credits roll over to the next month?
No. On RapidAPI, any unused credits do not carry over into the following month.

#### How much does each API call cost?
We use a credit-based pricing model rather than a flat per-call fee. The exact credit consumption varies by endpoint. For full details, please refer to our [documentation on credit usage](https://fdocs.info/api-reference/understanding-credit-usage).

#### How do I cancel my subscription?
You can cancel your subscription at any time through the RapidAPI dashboard. However, once you cancel, any remaining credits are immediately forfeited, and you will no longer have access to the API. We recommend canceling at the end of your billing cycle or after you have used all of your remaining credits.
